<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1155,788,987]" box="[160,409,788,814]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1155,788,987]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Body elongate, narrow, background colour translucent white, with red lines on dorsum from apex of rhinophores to tail, and on laterals from eyes; with white opaque dots scattered on dorsum. Cerata club-shaped, red in colour, with white punctuation more concentrated in apex. Rhinophores internally rolled, posterior part longer than anterior part, transparent white with opaque white dots.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="298" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1155,1036,1131]" box="[160,252,1036,1062]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1155,1036,1131]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
Specimens found feeding and mating on the red alga 
<taxonomicName authority="(C. Agardh) Nageli, 1847" authorityName="Nageli" authorityYear="1847" baseAuthorityName="C. Agardh" class="Florideophyceae" family="Ceramiaceae" genus="Antithamnion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceramiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatum">
<emphasis box="[764,1030,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Antithamnion cruciatum</emphasis>
(C.Agardh) Nägeli, 1847
</taxonomicName>
and were active at night.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="298" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1157,1180,1344]" box="[160,300,1180,1206]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1157,1180,1344]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
The species description of this slug was from specimens in Atlantic waters of 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1107,1215,1240]" name="Morocco" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Morocco</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[160,249,1250,1275]" name="Senegal" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Senegal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pruvot-Fol A" box="[262,442,1250,1275]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref21976" refString="Pruvot-Fol A. 1953. Etude de quelques Opisthobranches de la cote Atlantique du Maroc et du Senegal. Travaux de l'Institut Scientifique Cherifien. 5: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1953">Pruvot-Fol 1953</bibRefCitation>
); also found in 
<collectingCountry box="[618,713,1250,1275]" name="Portugal" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[726,937,1250,1275]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1055,1250,1275]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="201 - 207" refId="ref18692" refString="Cervera JL, Garcia-Gomez JC. 1986. Moluscos opistobranquios del litoral occidental andaluz: nuevas aportaciones faunisticas. Iberus. 6: 201 - 207." type="journal article" year="1986">Cervera and García-Gómez 1986</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[478,545,1285,1310]" name="Spain" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Spain</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[562,737,1285,1310]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[754,871,1285,1310]" country="Spain" name="Andalucia" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Andalucía</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[889,968,1285,1310]" country="Spain" name="Galicia" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Galicia</collectingRegion>
, Cantabric Sea, Levantine coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[349,561,1319,1344]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[581,686,1319,1344]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ballesteros M &amp; Madrenas E &amp; Pontes M" box="[699,945,1319,1344]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref18028" refString="Ballesteros M, Madrenas E, Pontes M. 2016. Actualizacion del catalogo de los moluscos opistobranquios (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) de las costas catalanas. Spira. 6: 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2016">Ballesteros et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="298" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1156,1393,1627]" box="[160,262,1393,1419]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1393,1419]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[160,1156,1393,1627]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">
This species is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[544,634,1429,1454]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Hermaea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis box="[544,634,1429,1454]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">H. bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having more globular and rounded cerata, and more abundant white body punctuation (
<bibRefCitation author="Salvat F" box="[694,828,1463,1488]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="358 - 365" refId="ref22214" refString="Salvat F. 1968. Hermaea paucicirra Pruvot-Fol, 1953 (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Opisthobranchia, Sacoglossa). Bull Mus Natl d'Histoire Nat. 40: 358 - 365. Paris." type="journal article" year="1968">Salvat 1968</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pruvot-Fol" authorityYear="1953" box="[851,1067,1463,1488]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Hermaea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="paucicirra">
<emphasis box="[851,1067,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">Hermaea paucicirra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from its sympatric species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Caballer and Ortea" authorityYear="2015" box="[623,751,1498,1523]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Hermaea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cantabra">
<emphasis box="[623,751,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">H. cantabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a more opaque white body with a red mark on the eyes. Because the epidermal red pigmentation on the dorsum obscures the digestive gland as it also happens with the cerata, not as in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Caballer and Ortea 2015)" baseAuthorityName="Caballer and Ortea" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[160,585,1602,1627]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Hermaea" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cantabra">
<emphasis box="[160,288,1602,1627]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="298">H. cantabra</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Caballer M &amp; Ortea J" box="[301,576,1602,1627]" pageId="33" pageNumber="298" pagination="125 - 136" refId="ref18427" refString="Caballer M, Ortea J. 2015. New data on the genus Hermaea (Mollusca: Sacoglossa) in Europe, with the description of a new species from Spain. Rev Academia Can Cienc. 27: 125 - 136." type="journal article" year="2015">Caballer and Ortea 2015</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
